3.00	Mark_Mercuri	Mark Mercuri	Mark Mercuri (born 21 February 1974) was a professional Australian rules football player for Essendon. He played in the 1993 Grand final winning team which defeated Carlton. In 2000, a season where Essendon lost only one game, Mercuri was one of the premier players of the competition, and signed a 5-year contract, which ultimately only lasted for 4 years.	
